Applications in cardiac motion modeling from 4D MRI are highlighted, where such a framework could capture complex, anatomically plausible deformations across populations. To maintain information during dimensionality reduction, mutual information preservation can be incorporated via variational inference. This approach aims to achieve geometrically aware, uncertainty-calibrated models for use in biomechanics and digital twins.

