ic complexity. Applications include early detection of structural anomalies in neurodegeneration, personalized surgical simulation under variable tissue properties, and generative modeling of disease progression with uncertainty quantification. We demonstrate that AGIRF outperforms static-geometry models in capturing rare deformation modes and provides more accurate confidence bounds in longitudinal predictions.",
